        "content": "<p>A would like to argue for the following design decision: </p>\n<p>That is to have a main directory called <code>WorldVolume</code> and within that directory move the current <code>Space</code>, <code>Time</code> and <code>SpaceTime</code> directories. Currently the two former ones are in <code>ClassicalMechanics</code>, and the latter is in <code>Relativity</code>. I would also like it to include things like compact versions of <code>Time</code> (e.g. circular) etc. </p>\n<p>I understand that <code>WorldVolume</code> is a fairly niche name, and am happy to hear alternatives if people have them. The name  <code>WorldVolume</code> comes from Sigma models where you have fields <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ϕ</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Σ</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\phi : \\Sigma \\to M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ϕ</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Σ</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span>, here <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Σ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Sigma</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Σ</span></span></span></span> is the WorldVolume and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span> is the target space.</p>\n<p>I'd be happy to hear any comments on this.</p>",
